fields.verbose_description: Translation that cost less because no editing is performed on the Translation.
Comprehensive Desktop Publish (DTP) services provides layout and formatting of localized content.  Original source material required for best results.  This service requires Third Party Review.
Graphic/Image Localization services provides formatting/publishing of translated image content.

Third Party Review is a formatting QA check in addition to the translation, proofreading/editing and DTP process. Third Party Review services is best for heavily formatted documents that need a detailed format review in addition to linguistic and/or if your content is sensitive enough you’d like a third person to review it in addition to the translator and proofreader.
508 Compliance services is used to validate your material/content is in compliance with the Section 508 Amendment to the Rehabilitation Act of 1973.

Notarization services vary from one country as well as fees and postage costs.  Please specify your notary request in the specific instructions field.  Orders requesting notarization will require manual estimate and review.
Attestation provides you with a written document certifying the translation and proofreading was provided by a professional translator.   Typically one attestation is needed per language.

A certified, native-speaking attorney reviews your content for correct translation and identifies any unusual risk and liability issues according to our 10 point checklist. You are provided with a completed copy of this checklist along with items identified for escalation.  Estimates are based on the word count and calculated at a rate of $175-$225 per hour depending on the language/region. Additional rounds of revision or consultation may be provided at an additional charge.
